Reasoning: The paper deals with image segmentation and motility analysis of Caenorhabditis elegans, a model organism used in biology. The proposed method uses statistical models and machine learning techniques for automated segmentation and quantification of nematode movements. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is computer vision (cs.CV), followed by machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Robotics (cs.RO) and neural networks (cs.NE) are also possible sub-categories, as they are relevant to the study of locomotion and behavior of the nematode.
